Ketu.note: Shadbala is not defined for nodes in PyJHora.

D1.name: Adhi Yoga
D1.description: Natural benefics occupy 6th, 7th and 8th from Moon
D1.benefit: You may become a king or a minister or an army chief, depending on the strength of the planets involved

D1.name: Anaphaa Yoga
D1.description: There are planets other than Sun in the 12th house from Moon
D1.benefit: You will become a king with good looks. Your body is likely free from disease. You are a person of character and have great reputation. You are surrounded by comforts.

D1.name: Asubha Yoga
D1.description: Lagna has malefics or has “paapa kartari or maleefics in 12th and 2nd house from Lagna.
D1.benefit: One born with this yoga has many desires and is sinful and enjoys the wealth of others.

D1.name: Bhaarathi Yoga
D1.description: If the lord of the sign occupied in navamsa by 2nd, 5th or 11th lord exalted and joins the 9th lord, then this yoga is present.
D1.benefit: One born with this yoga is a great scholar. Person is intelligent, religious, good-looking and famous. Bhaarathi is another name of Saraswathi, the goddess of learning.

D1.name: Bheri Yoga
D1.description: ]If (1) the 9th lord is strong and (2) 1st, 2nd, 7th and 12th houses are occupied by planets, then this yoga is present. Alternately, this is yoga is present if (1) the 9th lord is strong and (2) Jupiter, Venus and lagna lord are in mutual quadrants.
D1.benefit: One born with this yoga is blessed with wealth, spouse and children. Person can be a king. Person has fame and character. Person is virtuous and religious. Person enjoys pleasures. Bheri means a kettledrum.

D1.name: Duradhara Yoga
D1.description: There are planets other than Sun in the 2nd and 12th houses from Moon.
D1.benefit: You will enjoy many pleasures. You are charitable. You will wealth and vehicles. You will have good servants.

D1.name: Harsha Yoga
D1.description: If the 6th lord occupies the 6th house, then this yoga is present.
D1.benefit: One born with this yoga is happy, strong, good-natured and invincible. Harsha means joyous.

D1.name: Maalaa Yoga
D1.description: Three quadrants are occupied by natural benefics.
D1.benefit: You will be always happy. You will have nice clothes, vehicles, luxuries and friendship of many women.

D1.name: Maalavya Yoga
D1.description: Venus is in a quadrant in own sign or exaltation sign.
D1.benefit: You are a great person of watery nature. You emit a lustre akin to moonlight. You enjoy tasty food. You have luxuries. You have excellent health. You are well-versed in arts.

D1.name: Nipuna Yoga
D1.description: Sun and Mercury are together (in one sign).
D1.benefit: You will be intelligent and skillful in all works. You will be well known, respected and happy.\n This yoga is the most powerful in divisional charts like D-10. In rasi chart also, it can give results if Mercury is not combust.

D1.name: Paasa Yoga
D1.description: The seven planets occupy exactly 5 distinct signs among them.
D1.benefit: One born with this yoga has the risk of being imprisoned. This person is capable in their work. This person is talkataive. This person has many servants. This person lacks character. Paasa means a noose.

D1.name: Sunaphaa Yoga
D1.description: There are planets other than Sun in the 2nd house from Moon
D1.benefit: You will become a king or an equal. You are intelligent, wealthy and famous. You will have self-earned wealth.

D1.name: Ubhayachara Yoga
D1.description: There are planets other than Moon in the 2nd and 12th houses from Sun
D1.benefit: You will have all comforts. You will be like a king or an equal

D1.name: Vesai Yoga
D1.description: There is a planet other than Moon in the 2nd house from Sun
D1.benefit: You will have a balanced outlook. You are truthful, tall and sluggish. You will be happy and comfortable even with little wealth.

D1.name: Vosi Yoga
D1.description: There is a planet other than Moon in the 12th house from Sun
D1.benefit: You will be skillful, charitable, famous, learned and strong.

D144.name: Chatra Yoga
D144.description: All the planets occupy the 7 signs from the 7th house.
D144.benefit: One born with this yoga will help his people. This person is kind and liked by many kings. This person is intelligent. This person is happy in the early and late parts of life. This person is longlived. Chatra means an umbrella.

D40.name: Ardha Chandra Yoga
D40.description: All the planets occupy the 7 signs starting from a panapara or an apoklima.
D40.benefit: One born with this yoga becomes an army chief. This person has a good physique. Kings like this person. This person is strong and possesses gems, gold and many ornaments. Ardha Chandra means half-Moon.

D40.name: Naukaa Yoga
D40.description: All the planets occupy the 7 signs from lagna.
D40.benefit: One born with this yoga make money on things related to water. They have many desires. They are well-known. They are wicked, rough and miserly. Naukaa means a ship.

D8.name: Kemadruma Yoga
D8.description: There are no planets other than Sun in the 1st, 2nd and 12th houses from Moon and there are no planets other than Moon in the quadrants from lagna
D8.benefit: You are unlucky, bereft of intelligence and learning and afflicted by poverty and trouble. This bad yoga kills the results of other good yogas in the chart, especially Chandra yogas (if any). You have to work hard and succeed through great efforts.

D8.name: Soola Yoga
D8.description: The seven planets occupy exactly 3 distinct signs among them.
D8.benefit: One born with this yoga is sharp, lazy, violent, poor, prohibited and valiant. They win accolades in wars. Soola is Shiva’s weapon.

D8.name: Vidyut Yoga
D8.description: If (1) the 11th lord is in deep exaltation, (2) he joins Venus, and, (3) the two of them are in a quadrant from lagna lord, then this yoga is present.
D8.benefit: One born with this yoga becomes a king or an equal. Person is wealthy, pleasure-loving and charitable. Vidyut means a lightning bolt or electricity.

D2.name: Brahma Yoga
D2.description: If benefics occupy the 4th, 10th and 11th houses counted from lagna lord, then this yoga is present. Another variation of Brahma yoga: If (1) Jupiter is in a quadrant from the 9th lord, (2) Venus is in a quadrant from the 11th lord, and, (3) Mercury is in a quadrant from the 1st lord or 10th lord, then this yoga is present.
D2.benefit: One born with this yoga is happy, learned and blessed with wealth and children. Brahma is the creator of this universe. Lagna rules birth and the Creator is represented in a chart by lagna lord.

D2.name: Daama Yoga
D2.description: The seven planets occupy exactly 6 distinct signs among them.
D2.benefit: One born with this yoga is very rich and famous. This person has many children. This person has many gems. This person helps others. Daama means a wreath. Some authors call this Daamini yoga.

D2.name: Matsya Yoga
D2.description: If (1) benefics are in lagna and 9th, (2) some planets are in 5th, and, (3) malefics are in chaturasras (4th and 8th houses), then this yoga is present.
D2.benefit: One born with this yoga becomes an astrologer or a seer. Person is a personification of kindness, character and intelligence. Person is strong and good-looking. Person is famous and learned. Person is a tapasvi (austere pursuer). Matsya means a fish.

D2.name: Mridanga Yoga
D2.description: If (1) there are planets in own and exaltation signs in quadrants and trines and (2) lagna lord is strong, then this yoga is present.
D2.benefit: One born with this yoga is a king or an equal and is happy. Mridanga is a rich and elegant percussion instrument popular in south India.

D2.name: Parvata Yoga
D2.description: If (1) quadrants are occupied only by benefics and (2) the 7th and 8th houses are either vacant or occupied only by benefics
D2.benefit: One born with this yoga is fortunate, eloquent, famous, charitable, easy-going and likes humour. Parvata means a mountain.

D2.name: Subha Yoga
D2.description: Lagna has benefics or has “subha kartari – benefics in 12th and 2nd house from Lagna.
D2.benefit: One born with this yoga has eloquence, good looks and character

D2.name: Vajra Yoga
D2.description: Lagna and the 7th houses are occupied by natural benefic planet and the 4th and 10th houses are occupied by natural malefic planets.
D2.benefit: One born with this yoga is happy in the early and late parts of life. This person has valour. This person is not fortunate, but has no desires either. This person fights. Vajra means a diamond.

D6.name: Kaahala Yoga
D6.description: If (1) the 4th lord and Jupiter32 are in mutual quadrants and (2) lagna lord is strong, then this yoga is present. Alternately, this yoga is present if the 4th lord is exalted or in own sign and the 10th lord joins him.
D6.benefit: One born with this yoga is strong, bold, cunning and leads a large army. Person owns a few villages. Kaahala means excessive. It also means mischievous.

D6.name: Vasumati Yoga
D6.description: If benefics occupy upachayas, then this yoga is present.
D6.benefit: For it to give full results, malefics should not occupy upachayas and the benefics occupying upachayas should be strong. One born with this yoga has abundant wealth. Vasumati means earth.

D6.name: Veenaa Yoga
D6.description: The seven planets occupy exactly 7 distinct signs among them.
D6.benefit: One born with this yoga likes music, dance and songs. This person has many servants. This person is wealthy, skillful and a leader of men. Veenaa is a stringed musical instrument. This is also called Vallaki yoga by some authors.

D5.name: Sarpa Yoga
D5.description: Three quadrants are occupied by natural malefic planets.
D5.benefit: One born with this yoga is miserable, unhappy, cruel, poor and dependent on others for food. This is a very bad combination.

D5.name: Sasa Yoga
D5.description: Saturn should be in Capricorn, Aquariius or Libra and he should be in 1st, 4th, 7th or 10th from lagna
D5.benefit: You are a great person of airy nature. You are rabbit-like. You are wise and enjoy wandering. You are comfortable in forests, mountains and forts. You are valorous and have a slender build. You know the weaknesses of others. You are lively, but have some vacillation. You are charitable.

D108.name: Chaapa Yoga
D108.description: All the planets occupy the 7 signs from the 10th house.
D108.benefit: One born with this yoga becomes a liar, thief and a protector of secrets. This person wanders in forests. This person is unfortunate. This person is happy in the middle part of the life. Chaapa means a bow.

D108.name: Saraswathi Yoga
D108.description: If (1) each of Mercury, Jupiter and Venus occupies a quadrant or a trine or the 2nd house (not necessarily together) and (2) Jupiter is in an own or friendly or exaltation sign, then this yoga is present.
D108.benefit: One born with this yoga is very learned, skillful, intelligent, rich and famous. Person is praised by all. Saraswathi is the goddess of learning.

D3.name: Amala Yoga
D3.description: There are only natural benefics present in the 10th house from lagna or Moon.
D3.benefit: One born with this yoga has ever-lasting fame. The person is respected by kings. Person has luxuries and is virtuous. Person helps others. Amala means pure. Because the 10th house shows one's' conduct in society, situation of only benefics there makes one’s conduct in the society very pure.

D3.name: Chaamara Yoga
D3.description: If the lagna lord is exalted in a quadrant with Jupiter’s aspect or two benefics join in 7th, 9th or 10th, then this yoga is present.
D3.benefit: One born with this yoga is a king or someone respected by kings. Person is long-lived, scholarly, eloquent and learned in many arts. Chaamara means something akin to the plume on the head of a horse. By waving it, servants give relief to kings from heat (like a fan). It basically stands for the trappings of power.

D3.name: Hamsa Yoga
D3.description: Jupiter should be in Sagitarius, Pisces or Capricornn and he should be in 1st, 4th, 7th or 10th from lagna.
D3.benefit: You are a great man of ethery nature. You are swan-like. You have spiritual strength and purity. You are respected by everyone. You are very passionate. You may become a king. You may have all comforts. You enjoy life fully. You are a clever conversationalist and endowed with good speech.

D3.name: Sreenaatha Yoga
D3.description: If (1) the 7th lord is exalted in 10th and (2) 10th lord is with 9th lord, then this yoga is present.
D3.benefit: One born with this yoga becomes a great king equal to Indra – king of gods. Sreenaatha means the lord of great wealth and prosperity. It also means Vishnu.

D45.name: Trilochana Yoga
D45.description: If Sun, Moon and Mars are in mutual trines, then this yoga is present.
D45.benefit: One born with this yoga is wealthy, intelligent, long-lived and victorious over enemies. Person achieves everything without many obstacles. Trilochana means 'one with three eyes'. It is another name of Lord Siva, who has a hidden eye in His forehead.

D4.name: guru_mangala_yoga
D4.description: If Jupiter and Mars are together or in the 7th house from each other, then this yoga is present.
D4.benefit: One born with this yoga is righteous and energetic. The person's 'energies are channelled in dharmic paths.

D4.name: Kedaara Yoga
D4.description: The seven planets occupy exactly 4 distinct signs among them.
D4.benefit: One born with this yoga is an agriculturist. This person is happy wealthy and helpful to others. Kedaara means a field.

D30.name: Kalpadruma Yoga
D30.description: Consider (1) lagna lord, (2) his dispositor, (3) the latter’s dispositor in rasi and (4) in navamsa. If all the four planets are all in quadrants, trines or exaltation signs of both rasi and navamsa, then this yoga is present.
D30.benefit: One born with this yoga becomes a king. Person likes wars. Person is very prosperous, principled, strong and kind. Kalpadruma is a celestial tree of the heaven. This yoga is also known as Paarijaata yoga. Paarijaata is a celestial flower.

D30.name: Ruchaka Yoga
D30.description: Mars is in a quadrant in own sign or exaltation sign.
D30.benefit: You are a person of fiery nature. You have a lot of enthusiasm. You are a natural leader. You love to fight wars and you will be victorious over enemies. You are discriminative and a devotee of learned people. You are well-versed in occult sciences. You have good taste. You will be always successful.

D24.name: Sarala Yoga
D24.description: If the 8th lord occupies the 8th house, then this yoga is present.
D24.benefit: One born with this yoga is long-lived, fearless, learned, celebrated and prosperous. Person is a terror to his enemies. Sarala means straight-forward.

D11.name: Koorma Yoga
D11.description: If (1) the 5th, 6th and 7th houses are occupied by benefics who are in own, exaltation or friendly signs and (2) the 1st, 3rd and 11th houses are occupied by malefics who are in own or exaltation signs, then this yoga is present.
D11.benefit: One born with this yoga becomes a king. Person has piety and character. Person is happy, helpful and famous. Koorma means a tortoise.

D12.name: Bhadra Yoga
D12.description: Mercury is in a quadrant in own sign or exaltation sign.
D12.benefit: You are a person of earthy nature and are lion-like. You are learned in all respects. You have a good build of body and a deep voice. You have sattwa guna. You know yoga well. You are always surrounded by relatives, friends and family and enjoys your wealth with them. You maintain cleanliness in everything and are very systematic. You are a spirit of independence and religious.

D12.name: Gouri Yoga
D12.description: If the lord of the sign occupied in navamsa by the 10th lord is exalted in the 10th house and lagna lord joins him, then this yoga is present.
D12.benefit: One born with this yoga is from a respectable family and person is religious and virtuous. Person is blessed with happiness from family. Gouri is a form of Parvati – Lord Siva’s wife. She is an epitome of marital bliss and purity.

D12.name: Hari Yoga
D12.description: If benefics occupy the 2nd, 12th and 8th houses counted from the 2nd lord, then this yoga is present.
D12.benefit: One born with this yoga is happy, learned and blessed with wealth and children. Hari is a name of Lord Vishnu. The 2nd house is the house of food and money and it is a trine from karma sthana – the 10th house. It stands for sustenance and its lord represents Hari – Sustainer of Hindu Trinity – in a chart.

D9.name: Sankha Yoga
D9.description: If (1) lagna lord is strong and (2) 5th and 6th lords are in mutual quadrants, then this yoga is present. Alternately, this yoga is present if (1) lagna lord and 10th lord are together in a movable sign and (2) the 9th lord is strong.
D9.benefit: One born with this yoga is blessed with wealth, spouse and children. He is kind, pious, intelligent and long-lived. Sankha means a conch shell.

D7.name: Chandra Mangala Yoga
D7.description: Moon and Mars are together (in one sign).
D7.benefit: You are worldly wise and materially successful. You may earn money through unscrupulous means. You may treat mother or other women badly.
